{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Launch a public inquiry into the state of England's rivers",
        "additional_details": "A Public Inquiry must be launched to assess the problem, investigate those responsible and find a way forward.\r\n \r\nWater companies discharged 2.4 million hours of untreated sewage into our rivers in a single year, with 389,000 discharges in 2022 alone. Agricultural chemical runoff and plastic pollution have added to this problem, leading to a pollution that's killing our rivers.\r\n",
        "background": "The Environment Agency found that only 14% of Britain's rivers are in good ecological condition and none met the criteria for achieving \u2018good chemical status\u2019. Campaigners have declared some rivers to be 'ecologically dead'.",
